LINE.Text: 63% of Australians agree that religion does more harm
than good and only 44% agree that it is important to
Australia's moral life. However, we are not translating
this negativity to fear or dislike of individuals-84% are
completely comfortable being around people who have
different religious beliefs than their own. In this regard,
we are among the more tolerant nations globally, likely
a reflection of our multicultural society and more
positive views of immigration than many other nations.
